  "chapter": {
    "number": 11,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "The Root of Jesse"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Then a shoot will spring up from the stump of Jesse,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and a Branch from his roots will bear fruit.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The Spirit of the LORD will rest on Him—",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the Spirit of wisdom and understanding,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "the Spirit of counsel and strength,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "the Spirit of knowledge and fear of the LORD.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "And He will delight in the fear of the LORD.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "He will not judge by what His eyes see,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and He will not decide by what His ears hear,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "but with righteousness He will judge the poor,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and with equity He will decide for the lowly of the earth.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "He will strike the earth with the rod of His mouth",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and slay the wicked with the breath of His lips.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Righteousness will be the belt around His hips,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and faithfulness the sash around His waist.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The wolf will live with the lamb,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the leopard will lie down with the goat;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "the calf and young lion and fatling will be together,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2553
          },
          {
            "text": "and a little child will lead them.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The cow will graze with the bear,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "their young will lie down together,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and the lion will eat straw like the ox.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The infant will play by the cobra’s den,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the toddler will reach into the viper’s nest.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "They will neither harm nor destroy",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "on all My holy mountain,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "for the earth will be full of the knowledge of the LORD",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "as the sea is full of water.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          "On that day the Root of Jesse will stand as a banner for the peoples. The nations will seek Him,",
          {
            "noteId": 2554
          },
          "and His place of rest will be glorious."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          "On that day the Lord will extend His hand a second time to recover the remnant of His people from Assyria, from Egypt, from Pathros, from Cush,",
          {
            "noteId": 2555
          },
          "from Elam, from Shinar,",
          {
            "noteId": 2556
          },
          "from Hamath, and from the islands",
          {
            "noteId": 2557
          },
          "of the sea."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He will raise a banner for the nations",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and gather the exiles of Israel;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "He will collect the scattered of Judah",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "from the four corners of the earth.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Then the jealousy of Ephraim",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2558
          },
          {
            "text": "will depart,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the adversaries",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2559
          },
          {
            "text": "of Judah will be cut off.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Ephraim will no longer envy Judah,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "nor will Judah harass Ephraim.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "They will swoop down on the slopes of the Philistines to the west;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "together they will plunder the sons of the east.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "They will lay their hands on Edom and Moab,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the Ammonites will be subject to them.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The LORD will devote to destruction",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2560
          },
          {
            "text": "the gulf",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2561
          },
          {
            "text": "of the Sea of Egypt;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "with a scorching wind He will sweep His hand",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "over the Euphrates.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2562
          },
          {
            "text": "He will split it into seven streams",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "for men to cross with dry sandals.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 16,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "There will be a highway for the remnant of His people",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "who remain from Assyria,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "as there was for Israel",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "when they came up from the land of Egypt.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
